#architecture #overview

> Three-module layered design: parser → store → CLI, one-way data flow.

Three-module layered design. Each layer has a single responsibility and no
upward dependencies.

  eshp_parser.py  — pure parse/render, no I/O side effects
  eshp_store.py   — SQLite graph store, no CLI concerns
  eshp_cli.py     — Click commands, watchdog watcher, user output

Data flows one way: .eshp file → parse_eshp() → EshpNote → store.upsert_note() → SQLite.
The CLI is the only layer allowed to call both parser and store together.

.contains
-> parser
-> store
-> cli
